quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  64,10,"But those who do not believe and treat Our signs as falsehood, they will be companions of the fire, to dwell therein forever, and terrible is that destination"
  64,11,"No kind of calamity can occur except by the permission of God, and if anyone believes in God, God guides their heart, for God knows all things"
  64,12,"So follow God, and follow His messenger. But if you turn back, the duty of Our messenger is only to proclaim the message clearly and openly"
  64,13,"God, there is no god but He, therefore on God, let the believers put their trust"
  64,14,"O you who believe, indeed among your spouses and your children are enemies to you, so beware of them. And whether you forgive, overlook, or cover up their faults, indeed God is Oft-Forgiving, Mercifully Redeeming"
  64,15,"Your riches and your children may be only a trial, but in the presence of God is the highest reward"
  64,16,"So be conscious of God as much as you can. Listen, follow, and give in charity for the benefit of your own soul. And those saved from the greed of their own selves, they are the ones who achieve prosperity"
  64,17,"If you loan to God a handsome loan, He will double it to your credit, and He will grant you forgiveness. For God is most ready to appreciate service, Most Understanding"
  64,18,"Knower of what is open, Exalted in Might, Full of Wisdom"